emit(Events.PRODUCT_CREATED, ...)` is called\n2. `eventLog.push(...)` - sync\n3. First handler: analytics handler (sync) - runs, then `await undefined` yields\n4. Second handler: pricing handler - hasn't run yet!\n5. Control returns to `createProduct` which returns `id`\n\nThe `await undefined` in step 3 causes emit to yield before reaching the pricing handler! That's the bug. The pricing handler is the second handler for `PRODUCT_CREATED`, and it doesn't get to run because the `await` between handlers yields control back.\n\nSo the fix is in the test: I need to ensure the microtask queue is flushed before calling `pricing.getPrice`. Or I restructure the integration test to create pricing before analytics.\n\nLet me fix the test by adding `await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 0))` or using `await Promise.resolve()` multiple times. Actually, let me just fix the test ordering and add proper awaiting."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2164,"cache_read_input_tokens":42562,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2164},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"27ae9e91-eaa1-486f-81ac-6cc3839834ee","uuid":"7ba53007-6cab-4cb7-b6a3-81e8810950de"}
